The purpose of TAM Lab is to provide in-depth technology workshop sessions led by VMware Technical Account Managers (TAMs) to enable a culture of learning and partnership across the VMware organization. TAM Lab provides a platform for all to be hands-on with VMware and non-VMware technologies that will enable a stronger customer delivery through product knowledge and a greater technical resource network. All TAM Lab sessions are recorded for the purpose of creating a reference library for on-demand learning and enablement.

While TAM Lab is coordinated and led by volunteers from the TAM organization (individual contributors and leadership), any VMware employee is welcome to join TAM Lab sessions live or on-demand.
TAM Lab sessions are led by volunteer TAMs who can provide product/technology expertise and/or experience with a particular solution. In addition, a home lab environment is necessary for each session.
